  '<h1>Quality Contract</h1>',
  '<p>Every blamejs release passes a layered gate at <code>test/layer-0-primitives/codebase-patterns.test.js</code> that scans the framework\'s own <code>lib/</code> source. The gate exists so bug classes the framework has already swept once can\'t drift back in — not via direct re-introduction, not via a new file written from muscle memory, not via a slow proliferation across modules until someone notices the cluster.</p>',
  '<p>The gate has three layers, each catching a different proliferation distance:</p>',

